message: Philip was a Dartmouth [[Naval cadet]] in summer '39, thus not yet a member of the British Navy when he left for Greece. His mother/grandmother correspondence is clear: he left England to take up his role as a prince in Greece. Dickie opposed Philip even visiting Athens & when Alice admitted to him it was permanent, within days George II "inexplicably" ordered her to send him back to enroll in the British Navy. Wording shouldn't imply Philip's plan was to live or have career in UK
"Serenity" is not what the Encyclopedia says is the literal translation

He'd finished Gordonstoun Easter '39, aged 17; Uncle Dickie had Naval Cadet Philip spend 22-23 July 39 with Lilibet at Dartmouth; he finished term & 11 Aug 39 left England with Alice for Greece; 14 Sep 39 Alice wrote Dickie he'd live in Greece henceforth; Greek king overrules Alice & Grandma Milford Haven, "sudden word from George II, instructing that he return to England and resume his training.”; 21 Sep 39 he leaves Athens, staying with Grandma in London until start of Fall term at Dartmouth.
